  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. NO Azure Functions for in-proc execution. Handler runs inside the BFF's `ServiceBusJobProcessor` BackgroundService.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-004">Job Contract pattern. `IJobHandler&lt;T&gt;` shape. Handler MUST be idempotent under at-least-once delivery. `CorrelationId` propagation. Document bytes / large payloads NOT in payload.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI registration via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension (or the existing job-handlers registration site). Module total ≤15 non-framework registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Handler injects `IActionEngineFacade` (PublicContracts) — NOT `IActionOrchestrationService` from task 041. Facade boundary preserved (G12).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-017">Run record status transitions canonical: `Queued → Running → Completed | Failed | Poisoned | Cancelled`. Handler does NOT invent states; uses the orchestrator's transitions and translates final status to `JobOutcome`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors surfaced via `JobOutcome.Failed` / `JobOutcome.Poisoned` — NOT thrown out of `HandleAsync`. The `ServiceBusJobProcessor` translates outcomes to Service Bus message handling (complete / abandon / dead-letter).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages without budget verification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF, publish-size delta verified, no new CRUD→AI direct dependencies (facade enforced), no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Scheduler integration follows the task 001 runtime ADR (Azure-native scheduler choice). Handler shape is invariant under that choice; only the message-enqueue surface differs.</constraint>
  </constraints>

