  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Confirm task 001 (runtime ADR) and task 041 (orchestrator) both show ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. Load the task 001 runtime ADR draft to confirm the scheduler choice. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Load `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` and answer the pre-merge checklist in `notes/decisions/task-042-bff-extensions-checklist.md`. Cite placement = BFF (spec.md §6) and scheduler topology cite (task 001 runtime ADR).</step>
    <step order="2">Read the existing `IJobHandler.cs` + `ServiceBusJobProcessor.cs` + `IIdempotencyService.cs` + `RecordSyncJob.cs` + `JobOutcome.cs` to capture the handler shape. Note the dispatcher discovers handlers by type — no manual wiring.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Services/Jobs/ScheduledActionDispatchJob.cs`. Fields per `&lt;goal&gt;` section. JSON-serializable. Include the deterministic `IdempotencyKey` property (computed if not explicitly set: `$"action-dispatch:{ActionId}:{ScheduledForUtc:yyyyMMddHHmm}"`). Do NOT inline large payloads — small parameter values only (e.g., a Matter id, a recipient hint). Document bytes referenced by id ONLY.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `Services/Jobs/ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.cs`. Constructor-inject `IActionEngineFacade`, `IIdempotencyService`, `ILogger&lt;ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler&gt;`. Implement `HandleAsync(job, ct)`:
      (a) Idempotency reservation; if already reserved → return `JobOutcome.Skipped`;
      (b) Load Action via `IActionEngineFacade.GetActionAsync(job.ActionId, ct)`; if not found → `JobOutcome.Poisoned` (Action was deleted between schedule and dispatch);
      (c) Build `ActionExecutionContext` with `invocationSource = ScheduledJob`, the correlation id from the job, `tenantId`, `callerOid = "system:scheduler"`;
      (d) Call `IActionEngineFacade.ExecuteActionAsync(action, job.ParameterValues, context, ct)`;
      (e) Translate result: `Completed` → `JobOutcome.Succeeded`; `Failed` (transient — task 041 surfaces a flag) → `JobOutcome.Failed` (retryable); `Failed` (permanent) / `GateRejectedException` / `PhaseToolDeniedException` → `JobOutcome.Poisoned`; `Cancelled` → `JobOutcome.Succeeded` (cancellation is a clean exit per ADR-017).</step>
    <step order="5">DI registration: add `services.AddScoped&lt;IJobHandler&lt;ScheduledActionDispatchJob&gt;, ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler&gt;();` to `AddActionEngineModule()`. Confirm total non-framework registrations ≤15 per ADR-010.</step>
    <step order="6">Scheduler integration: per the task 001 runtime ADR, ensure the chosen scheduler enqueues `ScheduledActionDispatchJob` messages to the BFF's job Service Bus queue. The infrastructure piece (Bicep / SB topic + scheduled message / Logic App / etc.) lands in `infra/` per the runtime ADR's path. This task creates the handler shape but does NOT itself provision Azure resources — that's task 064 (BFF + Dataverse deploy) for production rollout.</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit tests:
      (a) Idempotency: two messages with same `IdempotencyKey` produce one Run record (second returns `Skipped`);
      (b) Action-not-found returns `Poisoned`;
      (c) Orchestrator-throws-`GateRejectedException` returns `Poisoned`;
      (d) Orchestrator-returns-`Completed` returns `Succeeded`;
      (e) Cancellation returns `Succeeded` per ADR-017 (cancellation is clean).</step>
    <step order="8">Write the integration test for FR-20 (Send weekly task digest): enqueue a `ScheduledActionDispatchJob` for the digest template, drive it through `ServiceBusJobProcessor`, assert a `sprk_actionrun` record exists in `Completed` state, assert idempotency replay returns `Skipped` without creating a duplicate run.</step>
    <step order="9">Run the G12 grep audit: `grep -rn "IActionOrchestrationService" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/` — expect NO matches. The handler reaches the orchestrator only through `IActionEngineFacade`. If a match shows, fix before Step 9.5.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the new job + handler + DI edit; `adr-check` verifies ADR-004 (handler shape, idempotency, correlation propagation, no document bytes), ADR-010 (registration via module extension), ADR-013 (facade boundary preserved), ADR-017 (canonical state transitions), ADR-019 (errors surface via `JobOutcome`, not thrown), ADR-029 (no new packages). Re-run `dotnet build` and unit + integration tests.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 042 ✅. Verify it unblocks tasks 052, 053, 054, 055, 060. Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-042-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

